Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA crazy human named Stephan walks around on all fours here.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a red bearded man. His shaggy hair is also red and he wears agrey kilt and robe.  It wouldn't be wise to fight this crazed lunatic.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA crazy old man is here, screaming something about Chaos.``
Mobiles.Description: The crazy old man looks like just that, with grey dishevelled hair, andsagging skin.  He blabbers about danger to come.  The question is, is hedelusional?

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA reflection of mirrored light wavers here.``
Mobiles.Description: A reflection of mirrored light appears to be alive.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA rat scurries along the ground, gnawing away.``
Mobiles.Description: A furry, dirty rat scurries around the ground, foraging for food.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA skeletal servant stand unmoving before you.``
Mobiles.Description: This skeleton stands guard in front of the door.  It does not move andcompletely blocks you progress in that direction.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe mist swirls around an invisible creature, its warm breath evident close by.``
Mobiles.Description: Swirls in the mist tells of an unseen creature somewhere nearby,breathing, drawing closer...  Particles of dust levitates just above thefloor, illuminated by a light that seems to come from all around.  Somethingis near, be prepared for the worst.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA robed spectre haunts the temple, destroying anyone that dares to approach.``
Mobiles.Description: This is the mighty Spectre of Chaos.  An undead being who lived thousandsof years ago, the Spectre is an innately evil creature.  Dressed in flowingrobes, and holding an unnatural light, the Spectre is a creature to befeared and respected.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA water nymph stands here, flashing a seductive grin.``
Mobiles.Description: This water nymph is incredibly alluring.  A beautiful form, with deep,penetrating eyes, and the most seductive grin you have ever encountered.One could stare at her forever.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA big blob of crystal ooze quivers here, uninterested in the world.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a ooze, how else can you describe it. oooze!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA protector of the realm of Chaos broods here.``
Mobiles.Description: A pale warrior with a stern face patrols the Chaos guild here.  He is oneof the appointed to keep peace and order in this forsaken place.  He is cladin black plate armor with the symbol of chaos adorning the chest.  In hisright hand he wields an grim iron polearm with practiced easy.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hOzu, the master cleric of Chaos, is here.``
Mobiles.Description: Ozu, the master cleric of Chaos, is a mix of innate holiness and totalchaos.  He is rather lanky for a cleric, and has a flowing mane of wavybrown hair.  He appears rather able to master the art of fighting for adwarf.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hYou see a ghostly cook floating around here preparing non-existant meals.``
Mobiles.Description: You see right though this cook. This cook is wierd!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA cleric of the Chaos guard named Ryeal grins at you.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon this proud guard of Chaos and notice a twinkle in hismischievious eyes. He grins at you.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA student of Chaos stands here, eyes closed in concentration.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a dedicated student full of determination that someday they willunderstand Chaos.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe mistress of Chaos stands stern and regal.``
Mobiles.Description: Lolita, the mistress of Chaos has an innately evil presence about her.While she is not ugly by any means, she is far from attractive.  There issomething about her that inspires both fear and respect.  Whether that beher aged presence or her black eyes, one cannot be sure.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA member of Chaos is here, lurking in the shadows.``
Mobiles.Description: Its tough to get a steady glimpse of this being, who continually dartsfrom shadow to shadow.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hYou see a pile of 'lock' gold here.``
Mobiles.Description: You look at all the gold! wow! then you notice that it has a curved stingerand claws like a scorpian!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA towering skeleton clad in rotting silk sits by his desk here.``
Mobiles.Description: This undead being was once the master of Chaos.  Now Ennio just stalksthe remains of the guild, exacting revenge for his death on those foolenough to challenge him now.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hCyric the Shopkeeper is here, dusting the counter.``
Mobiles.Description: Cyric is a wily shopkeeper, obviously untainted by whatever has befallenthis guild.  Apparently, he still makes a profit.  He looks at you, and asksyou if you're going to do any business with him.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe mighty barkeep named Bhaal stands behind the counter here.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon a dark mysterous man. He has raindrops tattooed on his head.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA brown, mossy skeleton sits in a heap on its throne here.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon an ancient skeleton. It is rumored that those of Chaos used tobe trained and given practices with a certain skeleton on a Throne...

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA skeleton is mostly here, a former master of Chaos.``
Mobiles.Description: The skeletal master is as you would expect a skeleton to be.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA giant rat is here munching on some bones.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a HUGE rat! it is the biggest you have ever seen! quick kill itbefore it kills you!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe water appears distorted here.``
Mobiles.Description: The water beast is a magical personification created from water.  It iswithout a definite form, but it appears very dangerous.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hBaeleron the piper welcomes you to his domicile.``
Mobiles.Description: Baeleron the piper is a short, brooding human.  His face is covered withred stubble to match his flowing red mane.  He is well known in these partsfor his ability on the bagpipes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hAn enchanted stone statue of a lion licks its paws slowly.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon a great beast. This magical beast protects its owner at alltimes.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA hulking brute stands on guard here, waiting for someone worthy enough to fight him.``
Mobiles.Description: A giant of a man stands here, clad in heavy armor and shield.  His bodybulges of muscles.  But something is amiss, as you look closer, you noticethat he is missing skin in his face leaving the pale white bone underneathbare in a macabre display of undeath.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hTrog, legendary battlemaster of Chaos is here.``
Mobiles.Description: A big strong warrior, rippling with muscles, stands before you.  It isTrog, grand warrior of the Chaos clan.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA zombie is lumbering around here.``
Mobiles.Description: Covered in tatters and rags, this is the undead corpse of a human being.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe eerie, glowing eyes of this floating spectre is almost hypnotic.``
Mobiles.Description: Dressed in full battle regalia, this floating knight's eerie eyes almost put you ina trance.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hBoreus, Chaos swordsman, is here.``
Mobiles.Description: Boreus, the swordsman, is a stout, middle-aged dwarf.  Hair covers themajority of his body, and he appears capable of picking a fight as well asdefending imself.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA skeletal rat runs around in circles here.``
Mobiles.Description: You look at a rat that is a skeleton..how odd.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA transparent cook is here cooking dinner.``
Mobiles.Description: You think you see someone cooking but you see right through it!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hRadric, the weaponskeeper is leaning on a mighty club here.``
Mobiles.Description: Radric, the weaponskeeper is a large, battle-scarred man.  His sizeimplies sterngth and demands respect.  Hairless and tattooed on his head,Radric appears to be a force.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA poltergist is here throwing things at you!``
Mobiles.Description: You see a fierce poltergist.  This one has an attidude and seems to notlike you very much.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA proud smith named Quickblade forges an axe here.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a proud weaponsmith and smith here smiling and saying 'Death isfor those who stand to block Chaos.'

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hLord Inanno stands here, reciting an invocation.``
Mobiles.Description: Inanno, Lord of Chaos mages, has been studying magics for hundreds ofyears.  Despite that age, he appears as fit and virile as those a tenth ofhis age.  He has mastered all forms of magic, and is more than a formidablefoe.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA faint flicker of motion gives away the presence of a servant lurking in the shadows.``
Mobiles.Description: You see the outline of what appears to be a person but you really can'ttell what it is you are looking at.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA young mage sits here learning about Chaos and magic.``
Mobiles.Description: This mage is diligently working on an old manuscript, translating theancient words and scribbling the finished product down in his journal.  Hisgrey cloak marks him as being an apprentice of the Chaos guild.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA black-skinned demon charges at you!``
Mobiles.Description: The fanged, gaping mouth of this demon snaps at you as you try to fend himoff.  All your attacks seem to be in vain as he shrugs them off, seeminglywithout feeling a thing.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hAn alchemist is here mixing chemicals in a bubbling cauldron.``
Mobiles.Description: You see a wise female mage. She is very pretty but you realize that shelikes to play with chemicals cause that is what she does best.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA beautiful mage flots cross-legged in the middle of the room.``
Mobiles.Description: Every inch of this quiet woman radiates a commanding power, her lithebody is accentuated by her flowing silk dress and the thin red belt aroundher waist.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hLord Daagar is here casting spells.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon the new headmaster of the mages school of Chaos magic.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hPrismatic light illuminates the room here.``
Mobiles.Description: You look upon rainbows of bright color and begin to get very dizzy!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hThe shadows waver as if alive.``
Mobiles.Description: You look into the darkness....

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hA shaggy man stands here drooling on himself.``
Mobiles.Description: His hair is disheveled and yellow green spittle flies out of his mouth ashe considers you balefully.  With a lick of his hands, he prepares his razorsharp claws for some cutting, and gets ready to FOK you up.

Mobiles.LongDescription: `hSomething is moving around on the shelves here...``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `aThis room is ostensibly barren.  The expected decayed furnishing isnonexistent.  It would appear that someone or something has purged this roomof all signs of inhabitance.  A pungent odor is prevalent, and there is astrange presence in the room.  There is a doorway to the south.``

`aThis is a very large domicile, apparently once a dormitory for thewarriors of Chaos.  There is a small squared circle in the center of theroom, likely where these warriors amused themselves with wrestling matches.There is an unsettling presence in the room.``

`aYou stand in a grand hallway.  You look at all the work and dedicationthat it must have taken to construct such a hallway.  Carved figures, whichrepresent warriors of every race, stand proudly with swords raised in atoast to you.  Gold and silver line the hallway and you see images ofdragons and knights floating in the air.  The knights seem to be fightingthe good dragons and riding on the backs of the evil red and black dragons.This place must have inspired the most hearty of evil warriors.  The hallstretches east and west, with a door on the north side.``

`aIn this room, the linens seems to have fared better than the furniture.The bedframe appears to have completely rotted away but some remnants of thesheets and a lump that may be the remains of a pillow still survive.  ``

`aYou stand in a grand hallway.  You look at all the work and dedicationthat it must have taken to construct such a hallway.  Carved figures, whichrepresent warriors of every race, stand proudly with swords raised in atoast to you.  Gold and silver line the hallway and you see holograms ofdragons and knights floating in the air.  The knights seems to be fightingthe good dragons and riding on the backs of the evil red and black dragons.This place must have inspired the most hearty of evil warriors!  The hallcontinues to the east, while a door leads to the north.``
`aThis room is rather nondescript, other than a massive pile of bones onthe floor.  The bones are not those of a known sensient being, as they areconsiderably too small.``

`aThis large room is filled with rows of stone tables and benchesrunning down both sides. The lighting here, although still rather dim,is better than in the rest of this immense complex. Strangely, the roomdoes not feel empty. If you are quiet, you can almost hear the murmuringof many voices in the misty gloom. There are decorative carvings on thewalls. You hear voices inside your head, stories of warriors in battlesand of fights with dragons. You feel completely at home here. Then onemore voice enters your head..."You are part of an eternal tradition."``

`aThis large room was obviously designed to prepare food for a mobof growing boys. There are two immense cooking hearths in this room, withkettles on them that would each hold enough food to feed a small army. Themost notable thing about this kitchen, however, is the group of peopleworking at the hearths and tables. If they weren't partially transparent,you would almost think they were alive- but they are, of course, merelynot dead.``

`aThis room appears to have been used to store food and suppliesfor the kitchen, and the crusted remains of the supplies and old clothsare clearly visible. Aside from the fact that it is strangely cool in here,it seems of little interest.``

`aYou stand in a large room.  A counter runs down the center of thisroom.  There area is well lighted and the counter has small holes, almostlike inkwells, at intervals along it.  This is where the students would comeand check out various weapons.  ``

`aThis room has falling racks containing pieces of nearly every sort ofarmour, from rotting leather to corroded pieces of plate.  There is even aheap of debris to the north that looks as if it were once a rack of shields.The remnants of armour may have once been neat and orderly.  Now they arescattered as if a great wind had struck this room.  ``

`aThe contents of this room are even more decrepit and deteriorated thanwhat you have already seen.  This room is full of rotted racks holding thedecayed remnants of missile weapons.  Obviously the components of bows andslings are more perishable than those of swords and armour.  As you standsurveying the residue, an old rusted dagger flies by, narrowly missing yourhead!  ``

`aThis room is filled with the debris of what apparently used to be racksof weapons.  At first glance it seems obvious that any weapons that remainhave long ago deteriorated into uselessness.  You see a Chaos Logo on thewall.  ``
`aThis room is recognizable as a weaponsmith shop to anyone who has everseen one.  From the forges along the wall to the hammers and tongs rackednext to them everything looks to be in its place.  ``

This immense room is laid out in lanes for crossbow and hurled weaponpractice. There are targets at the far north wall, and the room is marked indistances by numbers on the floor. The targets are attached to the ceilingand could be adjusted with pulleys from your position, if the ropes thatwent around the pulleys were not rotted away. The targets could be set upas suitable ranges for any type of practice, from thrown daggers to longbow.

`aThe Arena still continues its immense growth but seems differenthere. You see four statues in the corners of the arena, all which aremages with thier wands pointing to you. Suddenly you hear a voice..."So you think you are strong enough to best me? I know that is why youhave come to this place. And that is why I have been waiting here for you.For I am Stephan. Stephan, do you hear? The very name should make youtremble with fear. You silly little wretch will soon feel the power thatis mine to command! For mine is the only way. If you seek to leave thisplace you must go through me. Kill me if you dare!"``

`aThis room has pictures on the walls which seem to move of thier ownvalition.  They are pictures of mages, each in the act of casting a spell.Some of the spells you recognize, lightning bolt, fireball, but some arecompletely outside your experience.  The pictures seem to run through asequence in two or three minutes then begain again.  Each time that thepictures change though, the scene is slightly different: a variation inbackground, a different mage casting the spell, etc.  ``

`aThis room is filled with tables and benches formed from the stone ofthe floor itself.  They seem to have grown from the floor like some kind offungus.  It is clean and orderly and even appears to be free of dust.  ``
`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  ``

`aThis room is fairly typical of kitchens in this edifice, except thatthe hearth appears to burn without flame.  Tables and chairs are positionedabout the room,and very neatly at that.  There are doors in all directionssave east.  ``
`aThis room is ostensibly barren, except for a large pit in the middle ofthe room, apparently for trash.  A pungent odor fills the room, and a greymist hangs overhead.  ``

`aThis room is lined with shelves and filled with old rotten barrelswhich obviously once held the food for the kitchen.  It is surprisinglybright in here, considering that you saw no hint of a light until youstepped into this room.  You notice as you enter and exit the room that thelight dims and brightens with your presence.  It is very cold in here.  ``
`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  ``

`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  A ladder runs from a hole in thefloor through a hole in the ceiling.  ``

`aThis classroom is decorated in somber shades of gray and black and winered.  The shelves which line the walls contain skulls- dozens of skulls ofmany sizes.  This room is where the mages of Chaos came to be taught aboutdeath spells and the skulls were used to practice summoning the spirits ofthe dead.  ``
`aThis is the bedroom of a young mage.  It is very spartan, undecoratedsave for a plant situated below a hovering unnatural light.  ``
`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  ``
`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  ``

`aThis room is huge, as well it might be there are three protectivecircles here of differing types.  This room was obviously used for summoningcreatures from other planes.  Many scorch marks from fire and other magiclines the walls.  This must have at one time been a very important room.  ``

`aThis room has two long, wide tables against the north wall.  They arecovered with glassware and instruments of a mysterious nature.  The room isbrightly lit by two huge braziers filled with bright blue flames.  Younotice that the floor is covered with weird patterns, probably remnants fromlab experiments.  ``

`aThis room is filled with a huge collection of books.  There must bethousands of volumes here, all in a remarkable state of preservation.  Thereis a large table and three chairs, also well preserved.  You can almost feelthe mystical energy in the air.  ``

`aThis room was once rather comfortably appointed with two beds and twochairs.  The carvings on the walls are tasteful and soothing to the eye.There is a fireplace on the west wall, and a muted yellow flame burns in thehearth.  Although you sense no fuel or smoke, the fire seems to give off apleasant warmth that is welcome in these stone halls.  ``

`aThis room is a calm and quiet place, much at odds with the Chaosof the rest of this area. There is a bed, a desk, and two chairs groupedaround the empty fireplace, all which seem to have once been made of finematerials. Whoever loved here had very rich taste. In fact, he may stillbe here- there is a long decayed body on the bed, in the remnants of richrobes. A note is attached to the robes.``

`aThis room seems almost empty, except for the debris of desks andchairs.  But the walls seem to be of many different colors that shift andsway and sparkle.  The effect is almost hypnotic.  The colors keep swayingand moving...  ``
`aThis is a great magical hallway.  The air seems to be crisp and full ofmagic.  The walls are illuminated by glowing orbs of various colors andpictures of Chaos mages line the walls.  ``

`aThis room is lavishly decorated.  Many plush couches line the walls anda fur rug is set in front of a blazing hearth.  Desks and chairs also fit inthis room and you see pictures of beautiful scenes of pixies and nymphsdancing in the woods.  ``

`aThis room is filled with bookshelves.  They are loaded with what appearto be spellbooks and tomes on the arts of magic, which seem relativelyintact.  A large desk sits in the corner and a chair sits with it.  ``

`aThere are tables arranged thoughout the room with benches on one sideof them so that those seated would face the west wall. On the west wall isa raised dais with a flat black space behind it for drawing various diagrams.This appears to have been a classroom for young mages. In fact, there appearsto be a class in session at this moment. There is a robed form at the backof the class facing the wall, and a group of vague dark forms sitting atthe tables. You look more closely and see that it is really a ghost givinga lecture to a class of shadows.``

`aThis room looks very comfortable and is tidy. You see the remainsof an old desk and a bed in here and on the bed is a book. The book is ajournal that one of the students on this room kept of his studies.``

`aThis room looks as if it was once a remarkably comfortable room.  Theremains of four beds and four large armchairs still survive.  The room seemsto be much cleaner than anywhere else you have seen.  Perhaps some of theunseen servants take care of the chores.  ``

This is a sector of the forest that little is known about.  The sky seemseternally black.  Whether that is due to some unseen magic or the immensetrees overhead, one cannot say.  Vines drape down as arms waiting to grabfor anything, and this whole place seems rather eerie.
The forest path opens up here, leading to an unkepmt and overgrown path.There appears to be a tunnel dug out of the ground in the vicinity, butunder this drak sky, that could be an aberration.
This is the inside of a tunnel bored into the earth by some unknownforce.  There appears to be a deep descent ahead, and the only option toleave maybe to know return to the forest opening.

Sliding down the tunnel, hitting the ground at a point which climbingback up is impossible, you find yourself here.  There is nothing here butmud and rock, and it appears the only option is to keep going down.

`aThe end of the tunnel lands in a huge mirrored hall.  Some chaotic andtwisted force apparently placed these here as a discouragement to furtheradvancement.  Reflections of self stare around the room, and it appearsdifficult to naviagate to an exit.  ``

`aThe end of the tunnel lands in a huge mirrored hall.  Some chaotic andtwisted force apparently placed these here as a discouragement to furtheradvancement.  Reflections of self stare around the room, and it appearsdifficult to naviagate to an exit.  ``
`aThis is a dark room somewhere in the realm of Chaos.  Exits are barelyvisable, and rats scurry about the room.  ``
`aThis is another dark hallway.  Rats scurry about the room, and amephitis gas pervades the room.  ``
`aThe hallway lightens up here, but only slightly.  The contrast isenough to detect the immense size of this room.  There is a presence movingabout the hall, but it is too dark to detect.  ``
`aThe mist continues to make things nearly impossible to see, and thougha presence is definately in the area, there is no way you can see it.  ``
`aMore of the same misty darkness surrounds you, but there is a strongerpresence than ever in this room.  It appears a confrontation is inevitable. ``
`aThe mist dissapates here, but there is still a pervasive darkness tothe room.  There is no discernable beginning or end to this path but realityand perception are not always equivalent.  ``
`aThis room is almost entirely dark, and equally unavigable.  The onlyapparent way to find a path through this mess is by feel, but that may bevery dangerous in this region.  ``

`aThis area was obviously a temple, and there is still a massive altaragainst the center of the north wall.  Midway between the altar and theother three walls, the room is divided on three sides by massive floor toceiling columns.  It is lit by two huge braziers, which burn with aflickering purple flame, even though no fuel is visible, and appear to giveoff no heat.  In fact, this room is noticeably colder than the hallway fromwhich you just entered.  The room is huge, and there appear to be no exitsother than the doorway behind you.  ``

`aThis large room is decorated with carvings of young elves playing inpools of steaming water.  It seems strangely pleasant and quiet here.  Twostairways exit through the north wall, one on the west and one north.  ``

`aYou are in a softly lit room.  There are comfortable benches along thewalls and shelves for clothing and possessions.  The mirrors on the wall arequite small, but then again men don't look at the mirror all day.  ``

`aYou are in a softly lit room.  There are comfortable benches along thewalls and shelves for clothing and possessions.  The mirrors on the wall arequite large and an assortment of brushes and make-up line a counter.  ``

`aThis room is immense and looks like a park. The lighting is warm andsubdued, like a spring evening. The ground is covered with a green mossygrowth that seems soft enough to fall asleep on, and there is even a fountainwith a statue of a centaur. The pillars supporting the roof have been carvedinto the shapes of nymphs and dyads, and the entire room looks completelyinviting.``

`aYou can see very little in this room but clouds of fog, far denser thanthe mist which seems to permeate every inch of these corridors.  The room ispleasantly warm and steamy, and you can smell water.  Judging by the echo ofyour footsteps, the room is quite large.  ``

`aYou find yourself in a huge hallway, illuminated by torches burning oneither wall.  The floor is constructed from black marble, and the hallappears to overall well kept.  The hall stretches out to the north andsouth, and there are doorways to both the east and west.``

`aYou stand in an immense dining hall.  This room is 60' x 140' and islined with stone tables and attached benches.  In the center of the room isa huge statue of a Cleric holding a brass staff.  The floor is dirty andscuffed.  There is an exit to the south, and doors to the north and west.``

`aThe hall here gets wider and is supported by huge columns on bothsides.  The hall is lit by torches which burn a blue flame.  The floor ismade from fine black marble and is shiny.  The hall continues to the northand east, with doors to the south and west.  ``

Rooms.MaxMsg: The shopkeeper does not allow more than four customers at a time.
Rooms.EnterMsg: $n opens the door and steps through the archway.
Rooms.ExitMsg: $n pushes the door outwards, bidding you adieu.
Rooms.RoomDescription: `aYou have come upon a large shop.  A sign above the counter reads'Entropy--The Shop of Chaos'.  The walls of the store or adorned withpaintings of the legendary figures of the order of Chaos.  Peering upwards,you realize that there is no ceiling over this store, but just an opagueblack sky, stretching endlessly.  Far in above this store, black dragonsskirt about the sky.  Behind the counter, the shopkeeper prepares to serveyou.  ``

`aThe hallway here is very quiet.  The torches here burn an errie green.The marble floor here is scuffed and looks like it is in constant use.  Thecolumns are cracked and rubble lies on the ground.  To the south lies aconspicuous`o silver door``.

`aThis room is filled with decaying trophies.  The walls are covered withrusted and unusable weapons and the moldering heads of all manner of beasts.It appears as if someone had spent a lifetime in the pursuit of killing.  Atrapdoor in the floor leads to a lower level of the Abandonded Guild.  ``

`aYou are in an alcove with a strange marble statue in it, the likenessof an elf in long flowing robes.  He is holding out his hands with the palmsup as if to offer you something.  There is an inscription around the bottom.You also see a grand gate to the south.  ``

`aThis is the Chaos bar.  The ambience is both evil and magical, butoverly nondescript.  Other than the symbol of Chaos emblazed on the farwall, it looks like any other bar you've seen.  The barkeep ushers you tohave a drink.  ``

`aThis is the end of the dark hall.  It looks similar to the rest of thehall, except that the torch flames vary in color here.  The torches aligningthe walls alternate between blue and yellow, while the tourch adjacent tothe southern door burns green.  A faint, red, flickering glow can be seenthrough the cracks in the trapdoor below.  ``

`aYou have stepped into the Arena.  This is a vast place reaching fiftyfeet into the air and the whole chamber is so large that you cannot evencomprehend its immenseness because of the darkness.  Near you, you can makeout tiers of seats stretching up and around the walls.  You hear a cackle tothe west.  ``

In this room stands an ornate, archbacked throne, apparently carved outof a single block of stone.  It faces outwards, towards the door youentered.  The separated bones of a single human skeleton drift lazily inmidair above the seat of the throne, shifting about in an endless jumble.The skull moves but is always facing outwards and turning to look at you;the only bones that are not part of this endless, silent dance are the feetof the skeleton.  These are on the floor, positioned as if the skeleton weresitting on the throne.

`aThe warm, muted glow of two hooded lamps illuminates this cozy room.Furs cover the floor, and old wooden furniture lines the walls.  Thefurniture consists of a large eating table, a sideboard, three largereclining chairs woth foot-stools, a high stool and a desk.  Two shelf unitsare also along the walls, home to proudly displayed weapons and a few thickbooks.  On the far wall is a fireplace, a merry blaze crackling within it.It is surounded by an ornately-carved stone mantle depicting armored humanknights riding dragons and competing with elven knigts on Pegasi.  Overhead,the dragon and Pegasi riders motif is repeated on the carved panels of theceiling.  Brass cloak-hooks project from a human-sized arch of richlypolished wooden paneling just inside the door.  The arch-topped panelcontains a fold-down wooden bench, and is carved with a large, complex sceneof birds singing over a pool where a unicorn bends its head to drink.  Youdon't hear anything but the faint crackle of the fire.``

`aThis large room was obviously a kitchen, the place where meals wereprepared for the clerics and their students.  There are two large cookinghearths, one each on the north and west wall.  The smell of rotten foodfills this room.  ``
`aThis is a passage along the cleric's training hallway.  Rotten benchesalign themselves against the walls, below torches burning red.  Doors are tothe north and east.  ``
`aThis dimly lit room is lined with shelves, and is strangely cold.  Theshelves seem to be laden with many small, unidentifiable masses.  You cannot tell from here if any of them are moving.  ``

`aYou stand in the once busy hallway of the clerics of Chaos.  It washere that all the faithful of Chaos came to learn and practice theirbeliefs.  It is here that they learned both the ways of Chaos and the way ofFate.  There are gold and crystal chandeliers hanging on the ceiling.  Thehallway continues to the east and west, with doors in the other cardinaldirections.  ``

`aThis room is virtually empty.  Four piles of rotted wood and cloth arescattered in this room and may have once served as beds.  This seems to be adorm room for the Clerical students of Chaos.  The walls have many postersdepicting the God of Chaos and there is a desk against the northern wall.``

`aYou stand in the once busy hallway of the clerics of Chaos.  It washere that all the faithful of Chaos came to learn and practice theirbeliefs.  It is here that they learned both the ways of Chaos and the way ofFate.  There are gold and crystal chandeliers hanging on the ceiling.  Thehallway continues to the the east and west, with doorways on the north andsouth walls.  ``

`aThis room appears similar to the others, except that it appears thatsomeone or something has been cleaning up in here.  The furnishings arestill decayed, but the rotting piles have been neatly arranged.  It appearsas though someone or something has been doing some housekeeping in here.  ``

`aYou stand in the once busy hallway of the clerics of Chaos.  It washere that all the faithful of Chaos came to learn and practice theirbeliefs.  It is here that they learned both the ways of Chaos and the way ofFate.  There are gold and crystal chandeliers hanging on the ceiling.  Exitslead east and west.  There is a door to the north and a door to the southwith a painting of a skull on it.  ``

`aThis room appears like the others, misty and filled with crumblingfurniture, but it seems much brighter.  You can easily see the room and itsrotting furnishings-as well as a small glint, as from something bright,under some of the rotting wood.  ``

`aThis huge room is full of corroded metal bedframes, and there is adecaying cabinet in the northwest corner.  A strange looking glyph decoratesthe floor just inside the doorway.  You feel very calm in this room.  ``

`aYou find yourself in what serves as the library of Chaos.  This room islavishly decorated, with plush chairs and sofas throughout the room.  Largedesks are scattered through out the study, each equipped with pen andparchment.  Thousands of books pertsaining to the various disciplines ofChaos lie on ebony shelves along the walls.  The room appears to befrequented still.  ``

`aYou stand in the once busy hallway of the clerics of Chaos.  It washere that all the faithful of Chaos came to learn and practice theirbeliefs.  It is here that they learned both the ways of Chaos and the way ofFate.  There are gold and crystal chandeliers hanging on the ceiling.  Thehallway extends to the west with doors to the north and east.  ``

`aYou stand in the once busy hallway of the clerics of Chaos.  It washere that all the faithful of Chaos came to learn and practice theirbeliefs.  It is here that they learned both the ways of Chaos and the way ofFate.  There are gold and crystal chandeliers hanging on the ceiling.  Thehallway extends northwards with doors in all other cardinal directions.  ``

`aThis room is larger than the others but similarly appointed.  Whatremains of the furniture seems of better quality, but is still badlydecayed.  The room is uniformly dark and you are not casting any shadows.There is a large brass desk in the corner of the room and windows look outover a strange view.  ``

`aThis room appears to have been a sitting room of some kind.  There arethe remains of a sofa and two chairs near the north wall.  A decayed tableis in the northeast corner with a crystal decanter lying amongst the bitsand pieces.  ``

`aThis room appears to be where the students took breaks.  There is ahuge crystal ball in the center of the room.  There is also a decayedbedframe and some decomposed books on the floor.  A strange design on theeast wall appears to have been drawn in some type of thick paint, but youcannot make it out from here.  ``

`aThis room looks to be in a remarkable state of preservation.  Itcontains a perfectly made bed and some clerical robes hung neatly on hooksin the southeast corner.  Could it be that someone still lives here?  ``
`aTapestries woven with the images of fantastic and magical beasts linethe walls of this room.  Thick rugs resembling grass cover the floor.  Thereare no other furnishings in this room.  ``

`aThis chamber was at one time lushly decorated.  Glowing orbs of variouscolors float near the ceiling, illuminating the metal frame of what was oncea huge bed.  There is a large hearth against the north wall and a huge motheaten fur rug in front of it.  There is a door in the east end of the wall.``

`aThe plain stone walls of this chamber differ drastically from the roomjust outside.  Torches burn on the scarred walls and splashes of blood crossthe floor of this chamber.  In the middle of it sits a throne of ebony, atopwhich rests a drooling gibbering man.  His shirtless form shows his fearsomephysique and the claw upon his right arm trembles with the anticipation ofanother kill.  ``

A blue haze seems to rise before your very eyes, silently and rapidly,seperating the world around as you stare at the cryptic inscription.  Theinscription seems to consist of a number of names and other nonsense,followed by the last line, glowing in deep blue common lettering: "If you'rereading this, of course, its too late."  Blue radiance is everywhere; youare lost and floating somewhere not quite real.  Blue, shifting light isunder, over, and all around you.  The light begins to fade, and you realizethat your legs and feet are colder and wetter than the rest of you.  You'resomewhere else, all light goes black and you are standing in inky, darkwater as deep as your thighs.  A faint purple light comes from your left.Ahead of you, in the distance, you hear the water rippling as somethingwithin it moves...

`aYou stand in a grand hallway.  You look at all the work and dedicationthat it must have taken to construct such an atrium.  Carved figures, whichrepresent warriors of every race, stand proudly with swords raised in atoast to you.  Gold and silver line the hallway and you see images ofdragons and knights floating in the air.  The knights seem to be fightingthe good dragons and riding on the backs of the evil red and black dragons.This place must have inspired the most hearty of evil warriors.``

`aThe hallway here is very quiet.  The torches here burn an errie green.The marble floor here is scuffed and looks like it is in constant use.  Thecolumns are cracked and rubble lies on the ground.  ``
